The paper deals with the analysis and estimation of welfare in auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the use of data-driven techniques to estimate the empirical price of anarchy, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper applies these techniques to advertising auctions, which is a topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of simple properties of auctions to estimate the revenue covering parameter, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper applies these techniques to position auctions, which is a topic in mechanism design (cs.MA).
